.TH "ishtp_cl_send" 9 "ishtp_cl_send" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ishtp_cl_send \- Send a message to firmware
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ishtp_cl_send
.BI "(struct ishtp_cl *cl "  ","
.BI "uint8_t *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cl" 12
client device instance
.IP "buf" 12
message buffer
.IP "length" 12
length of message
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the client is correct state to send message, this function gets a buffer
from tx ring buffers, copy the message data and call to send the message
using \fBishtp_cl_send_msg\fP
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful or error code on failure
